column1: # This file contains the the physical locations of gene converted and
# non-gene-converted MPPs in oNCOs found in the probands of this study,
# along with information about the phased alleles of the parent who
# transmits the oNCO, the allele transmitted to the proband and the
# allele inherited from the other parent. The event_id matches the
# column with the same name in the data file oNCOs.tsv.
# The data columns are as follows:
# ptype (oNCO transmitting parent, P: paternal, M: maternal),
# mrktype (MPP variant type: snp or indel)
# gfa (grandfather allele = paternal allele of oNCO transmitting parent)
# gma (grandmother allele = maternal allele of oNCO transmitting parent)
# converted (whether MPP is converted or not)
# opa (other parent allele - other parent is homozygous)
